latestPosts.caption:
I’ve noticed something funny, every time I say I don’t like partying people act like it’s some shocking confession.

But here’s the thing: 

• Not everyone enjoys the same things, and that’s perfectly normal. I don’t feel the need to be out every weekend to prove I’m enjoying life. I am enjoying it just in my own way. I like going out when I feel like it: 

• When I’m genuinely happy, when work is fulfilling, when I want to celebrate something meaningful. I don’t need loud music and a crowd to express joy. 

• My version of joy shows up in the way I work, the way I speak, the energy I carry when I’m around people I trust. I wake up with purpose, I create with intention, and I love expressing myself in spaces where I feel connected.

• I’ve been a private person & that’s not something I’m changing or explaining away. I like to value my space, my peace, and the people I choose to share that with. Being selective with my energy isn’t cold, it’s just another way of living that do exists ❤️

And my version of it involves enjoying adventures, spontaneous plans, experiences that leave stories behind,  conversations that go beyond the surface. Where we talk about how we were raised, the kind of people our parents are, the little things that shaped us. That’s the kind of energy I connect with. A lot of talking, a lot of laughing, and a whole lot of meaning behind it that’s my version of joy. 🤌🏼🙌🏼
